10230270@unknown@formal@none@1@S@For example, in 1980, a company called "Don't Ask Software", founded by Randy Simon, created a version for the Apple II, Atari, and Commodore PCs, which verbally abused the user based on the user's input.@1@35@@oe@30-11-2008
